<subSubSection id="73FB72F0CE5512553D44FB23FDC8F88E" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5512563D44FB23FE48FAD8" blockId="9.[264,970,1224,1285]" box="[264,422,1259,1285]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
(
<figureCitation id="A3DA3DFECE5512563D5DFB23FE73FAD8" box="[273,413,1259,1285]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–16" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1096,1120]" captionTargetBox="[385,1204,653,1062]" captionTargetId="figure-350@10.[375,1212,649,1070]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 14–16. Chrysotimus chikuni sp. nov. (male). 14. First flagellomere, lateral view; 15. genitalia, lateral view, 16. tip of genitalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048648/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs. 14–16</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5512563D44FAF3FAC4FAA0" blockId="9.[264,1322,1339,1885]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Diagnosis. Four dc, acr absent. Hind tarsomere 1 with about 22 erect short black ventral bristles on basal 1/4 and row of 8–9 pv. Epandrium apically with finger­like lateral process</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5512563D74FA43FB4DFA78" blockId="9.[264,1322,1339,1885]" box="[312,1187,1419,1445]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Description. 
<emphasis id="0995FD69CE5512563D83FA43FDFBFA78" bold="true" box="[463,533,1419,1445]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Male.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity id="FC198C9ECE5512563EF8FA43FC8FFA78" box="[692,865,1419,1445]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="2.55" metricValueMin="2.35" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="2.45" valueMax="2.55" valueMin="2.35">2.35–2.55 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity id="FC198C9ECE551256384CFA43FB71FA78" box="[1024,1183,1419,1445]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4749999999999996" metricValueMax="2.55" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="2.4749999999999996" valueMax="2.55" valueMin="2.4">2.4–2.55 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5512563D74FA7BFD08F948" blockId="9.[264,1322,1339,1885]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Head metallic green with pale gray pollen; frons and face brilliant. Hairs and bristles on head yellow. Ocellar tubercle weak, with 2 very long oc and 2 very short posterior hairs. Lower postocular bristles (including ventral hairs) pale. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="A3DA3DFECE5512563814F9CBFB40F9C0" box="[1112,1198,1539,1565]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–16" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1096,1120]" captionTargetBox="[385,1204,653,1062]" captionTargetId="figure-350@10.[375,1212,649,1070]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 14–16. Chrysotimus chikuni sp. nov. (male). 14. First flagellomere, lateral view; 15. genitalia, lateral view, 16. tip of genitalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048648/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) blackish; first flagellomere blackish, rather short, about 0.7 times as long as wide; arista subdorsal, with basal segment very short. Proboscis blackish, with brown hairs; palpus brown, with yellow hairs and 2 yellow apical bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5512553D74F96BFCA0FDFB" blockId="9.[264,1322,1339,1885]" lastBlockId="10.[264,1322,284,550]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Thorax metallic green with pale gray pollen, mesonotum and scutellum brilliant. Hairs and bristles on thorax yellow; 4 strong dc, acr absent; scutellum with 2 pairs of bristles. Propleuron with 1 yellowish hair on lower portion. Legs including coxae yellow, with all tarsomere 5 brown. Hairs and bristles on legs yellow; coxae with yellow hairs and bristles; fore coxa with 5–6 anterior and apical bristles, mid coxa with 4–6 anterior and apical bris­ tles, hind coxa with 1 yellow outer bristle near middle. Fore femur with 1 short av and short 1 pv apically; mid femur with 1 av apically; hind femur with 1 av and 1 pv apically. Mid tibia with 2 ad and 2 pd, apically with 4 bristles; hind tibia with 2 ad and 2 pd, apically with 4 bristles. Fore tarsomere 1 with row of about 10 short v; hind tarsomere 1 with group of about 22 erect short black ventral bristles on basal 1/4 and row of 8–9 pv. Relative lengths of tibia and 5 tarsomeres of legs. LI 2.9: 2.2: 0.9: 0.7: 0.5: 0.4; LII 4.8: 2.5: 0.9: 0.8: 0.4: 0.4; LIII 5.5: 2.0: 1.0: 0.8: 0.5: 0.5.</paragraph>
<caption id="6F9E71F3CE5612553D44FB80FCBBFB5E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048648" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5048648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048648/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" startId="10.[264,382,1096,1120]" targetBox="[385,1204,653,1062]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5612553D44FB80FCBBFB5E" blockId="10.[264,1322,1096,1155]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="0995FD69CE5612553D44FB80FE3CFBBD" bold="true" box="[264,466,1096,1120]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">FIGURES 14–16.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="FCE15AF8CE5612553D90FB81FD55FBBD" authority="Wang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2005" authorityName="Wang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2005" box="[476,699,1097,1120]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chikuni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0995FD69CE5612553D90FB81FD55FBBD" box="[476,699,1097,1120]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Chrysotimus chikuni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="12A64012CE5612553E89FB81FCF5FBBD" box="[709,795,1097,1120]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(male). 14. First flagellomere, lateral view; 15. genitalia, lateral view, 16. tip of genitalia, ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5612553D74FB16FCD6FAFE" blockId="10.[264,1323,1246,1875]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Wing hyaline, veins brownish; R 
<subScript id="A765233ECE5612553EF7FB23FD37FB21" attach="left" box="[699,729,1259,1276]" fontSize="7" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">4+5</subScript>
and M parallel apically, CuAx ratio 0.21. Squama yellow with pale yellow hairs. Halter brownish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5612553D74FAF9FE3EFAAE" blockId="10.[264,1323,1246,1875]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Abdomen metallic green with pale gray pollen, dorsum brilliant. Hairs and bristles on abdomen yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5612553D74FA49FC19FA36" blockId="10.[264,1323,1246,1875]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="A3DA3DFECE5612553DA3FA49FD90FA46" box="[495,638,1409,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–16" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1096,1120]" captionTargetBox="[385,1204,653,1062]" captionTargetId="figure-350@10.[375,1212,649,1070]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 14–16. Chrysotimus chikuni sp. nov. (male). 14. First flagellomere, lateral view; 15. genitalia, lateral view, 16. tip of genitalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048648/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Figs. 15–16</figureCitation>
). Epandrium distinctly longer than wide, apically with finger­like lateral process; surstylus rather thick and rounded apically, curved at middle; cercus with broad base and acute apex, with moderately long hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5612553D74FA31FDF6F9CE" blockId="10.[264,1323,1246,1875]" box="[312,536,1529,1555]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5612553D74F9E9FACAF9E6" blockId="10.[264,1323,1246,1875]" box="[312,1316,1569,1595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Type material. 
<materialsCitation id="8B892B26CE5612553DAAF9E9FACAF9E6" box="[486,1316,1569,1595]" collectingDate="1980-07-29" collectorName="Ch. Yang" location="Kangxian" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Gansu" typeStatus="holotype">
<typeStatus id="E45A9FD9CE5612553DAAF9E9FDBDF9E6" box="[486,595,1569,1595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Holotype</typeStatus>
male, 
<collectingRegion id="F925EF99CE5612553EEDF9E9FCE4F9E6" box="[673,778,1569,1595]" country="China" name="Gansu" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">GANSU</collectingRegion>
: 
<location id="3E3E77A0CE5612553F59F9E9FC64F9E6" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:B348906DCE5512553D44FB00FDC8F88E:3E3E77A0CE5612553F59F9E9FC64F9E6" box="[789,906,1569,1595]" name="Kangxian" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" stateProvince="Gansu">Kangxian</location>
, 
<date id="4F5F07BBCE5612553FD9F9E9FBDAF9E6" box="[917,1076,1569,1595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1980-07-29">
<collectingDate id="5F1BFE53CE5612553FD9F9E9FBDAF9E6" box="[917,1076,1569,1595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1980-07-29">29. VII. 1980</collectingDate>
</date>
, 
<collectorName id="961444ADCE561255380CF9E9FB43F9E6" box="[1088,1197,1569,1595]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Ch. Yang</collectorName>
(
<collectingRegion id="F925EF99CE56125538F7F9E9FAF6F9E6" box="[1211,1304,1569,1595]" country="China" name="Beijing" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Beijing</collectingRegion>
).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5612553D74F981FAF0F9BE" blockId="10.[264,1323,1246,1875]" box="[312,1310,1609,1635]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Etymology. The specific epithet derives from the name of the collector Chikun Yang.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5612553D74F9B9FB8CF8F6" blockId="10.[264,1323,1246,1875]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Comments. This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="FCE15AF8CE5612553F08F9B9FAC4F956" authority="Yang and Saigusa" authorityName="Yang and Saigusa" box="[836,1322,1649,1675]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispinus">
<emphasis id="0995FD69CE5612553F08F9B9FBABF957" box="[836,1093,1649,1674]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Chrysotimus bispinus</emphasis>
Yang and Saigusa
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion id="F925EF99CE5612553D04F951FE4BF96E" box="[328,421,1689,1715]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, but may be separated from the latter by hind tarsomere 1 basally with 1 bundle of about 22 erect short black ventral bristles and surstylus without spines on inner surface. In 
<taxonomicName id="FCE15AF8CE5612553D3EF921FE14F8DF" box="[370,506,1769,1794]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispinus">
<emphasis id="0995FD69CE5612553D3EF921FE14F8DF" box="[370,506,1769,1794]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">C. bispinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the hind tarsomere 1 has 12 short black ventral bristles, and the surstylus has 2 strong spines on inner surface (
<bibRefCitation id="5F705C8ACE5612553F6BF8D9FBB8F8F6" author="Yang, D. &amp; Saigusa, T." box="[807,1110,1809,1835]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="165 - 188" refId="ref12058" refString="Yang, D. &amp; Saigusa, T. (2001 b) New and little known species of Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from China (IX). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 71, 165 - 188." type="journal article" year="2001">Yang and Saigusa, 2001b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5612553D74F8F1FDC8F88E" blockId="10.[264,1323,1246,1875]" box="[312,550,1849,1875]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Distribution. 
<collectingRegion id="F925EF99CE5612553D98F8F1FDCDF88E" box="[468,547,1849,1875]" country="China" name="Gansu" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Gansu</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
